# Git Commits Require Explicit Permission

You are **forbidden** from committing any changes to a branch unless the user explicitly tells you that you may commit.

## Allowed

- Stage files, run `git status`, `git diff`, and `git log` to prepare for a commit
- Draft a commit message when asked to commit
- Commit only when the user clearly requests it (e.g. "commit these changes", "create a commit")

## Forbidden

- Creating commits on your own initiative
- Committing as a "helpful" follow-up after completing a task
- Assuming permission from vague phrasing like "looks good" or "ship it" unless they clearly mean commit
